## 🕹️ How to use 

## Minigame Tab

This tab automatically solves the **QTE minigame**—that circle with a letter that appears when a chest or other rare item appears.

⚠️I STRONGLY RECOMMEND USING ONE OF THE TWO RESOLUTIONS BELOW⚠️
⚠️IF YOU USE ONE OF THE RESOLUTIONS BELOW, USE THE COORDINATES I’M PROVIDING; IT WILL BE EASIER TO USE THE MACRO.⚠️


RESOLUTION 1920 X 1080: 924 499 71 75 🟪
RESOLUTION 1360 X 768: 654 347 54 64  🟪



**How to set it up if you can’t use these two resolutions:**

1. Log into Bridger Western and go to a fishing spot
2. Open JesterHub and go to the **Minigame** tab
3. Wait until a minigame appears, then click the “Define” button, and select an area ONLY around the letter appearing in the minigame—do not select the entire circle or a large area.


**Minigame tab options:**

- **Speed**.
- **Blocked keys:** Letters that the macro will never press. Example: enter `CQ` to never press C or Q.
- **Detection area:** In the Detection area, you enter the coords that i left on the beging of this guide 

### Auto Fish Tab


**Sensitivity:**

The sensitivity slider controls how “sensitive” the macro is to detecting a bite:

- **(To the left):** Detects more easily — may pick up false sounds in noisy environments
- **(To the right):** Only triggers on sounds very similar to a bite — recommended if the macro is giving false positives
- If you're experiencing a lot of false positives, you can try calibrating the bite detection using the sensitivity slider, and also by recording the sound of a fish biting using the record button (this makes it more accurate).


